title: Purchasing power change in the Netherlands 2015 to 2020
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Year on year percentage change, with a total of 6 data points. The chart has 4 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly negative which exists from 2017 to 2015.
Differently, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2020 to 2019.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2019 to 2018.
Additionally, the next significant trend is slightly neutral which exists from 2018 to 2017.
